            "question": {
                "text": "Consider a quadratic equation x2 - 13x + 36 = 0 with \ncoefficients in a base b. The solutions of this equation \nin the same base b are x = 5 and x = 6. Then b =_____.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "8"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Given the base of quadratic equation is b. \n\n(1)b x2 - (13)b x + (36)b = (0)b \n\nx2 - (b + 3)x + 3b + 6 = 0 \n\nLet x = 5 \n\n25 - (b + 3)5 + 3b + 6 = 0 \n\n25 - 5b - 15 + 3b + 6 = 0 \n\n                      16 - 2b = 0 \n\n                               b = 8 \n\nLet x = 6 \n\n36 - (b + 3)6 + 3b + 6 = 0 \n\n36 - 6b - 18 + 3b + 6 = 0 \n\n                      24 - 3b = 0 \n\n                               b = 8 \n\nHence correct answer is (8).",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
